text:
111th Street, west side, south from 56th to Corona Avenues. The "Tourists" signs and the "Park Here" signs as well as the souvenirs booth are for the enticement of visitors to the New York World's Fair of 1939-40. Owners of empty lots in this area profited by converting them into auto parking spaces for Fair visitors.

P. L. Sperr
June 23, 1940
